===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|blessen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|bletsian|blētsian|lang=ang}}, {{term|bledsian|blēdsian|to consecrate ''(with blood)''|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|blōþisōjanan|to sprinkle, mark or hallow with blood|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Germanic|title=|blōdam|blood|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|bhlo-to-|to gush, spurt|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|title=|bhol-, *bhlē-dh-, *bhlō(w)-|to thrive, flourish, bloom|lang=en}}. Cognate with Old {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|bletza||to bless|tr=Modern {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|blessa|lang=is|lang=is}}}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|bledan|blēdan|to bleed|lang=ang}}. More at {{l|en|bleed}}.

